String Methods
1. str.length - how long is the string
2. str.charAt(index) - retrieves the character at the specified index
3. concat(str1, str2, ...) - combines two or more strings
4. str.indexOf(substr) - retrieves the index of the first occurrence of the specified substring
5. str.substring(startIndex, endIndex) - retrieves the characters between two specified indices (endIndex is optional)
6. str.slice(negativeIndex) - starts counting at the right to the left of the string
7. str.toUpperCase() - converts string to uppercase
8. str.toLowerCase() - converst string to lowercase
9. str.trim() - removes whitespace from both ends of a string
10. str.replace(oldValue, newValue) - replaces a specified value with another value in a string
11. template strings
`${stringVar}` - allows you to embed variables and expressions in a string
